    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm trying to build neovim from source on an old 32-bit computer (Toshiba Portege M400 with an Intel T2400) running Ubuntu 16.04.7.\n\nI'm following the [build instructions](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/BUILD.md). I've installed the dependencies:\n\n```\nwill@Portege-Ubuntu:~/code/neovim$ make --version\nGNU Make 4.1\nBuilt for i686-pc-linux-gnu\nCopyright (C) 1988-2014 Free Software Foundation, Inc.\nLicense GPLv3+: GNU GPL version 3 or later <http://gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html>\nThis is free software: you are free to change and redistribute it.\nThere is NO WARRANTY, to the extent permitted by law.\n\nwill@Portege-Ubuntu:~/code/neovim$ cmake --version\ncmake version 4.0.20250414-ged7f1c5\n\nCMake suite maintained and supported by Kitware (kitware.com/cmake).\n```\n\n`cmake --system-information` output available on request :)\n\nI'm trying to install the current latest [stable](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/a99c469e547fc59472d6d105c0fae323958297a1): \n\n```\nwill@Portege-Ubuntu:~/code/neovim$ git rev-parse HEAD\na99c469e547fc59472d6d105c0fae323958297a1\n```\n\nWhen I run `make distclean && make CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release` I get this error:\n\n```\n...\n[111/112] Performing install step for 'luv'\n[1/1] Install the project...\n-- Install configuration: \"Release\"\n-- Installing: /home/will/code/neovim/.deps/usr/lib/libluv.a\n-- Installing: /home/will/code/neovim/.deps/usr/include/luv/luv.h\n-- Installing: /home/will/code/neovim/.deps/usr/include/luv/util.h\n-- Installing: /home/will/code/neovim/.deps/usr/include/luv/lhandle.h\n-- Installing: /home/will/code/neovim/.deps/usr/include/luv/lreq.h\n[112/112] Completed 'luv'\n/usr/local/bin/cmake -B build -G \"Ninja\" -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release  /home/will/code/neovim/\nCMake Error: The source directory \"/home/will/code/neovim/.deps\" does not appear to contain CMakeLists.txt.\nSpecify --help for usage, or press the help button on the CMake GUI.\nMakefile:103: recipe for target 'build/.ran-cmake' failed\nmake: *** [build/.ran-cmake] Error 1\n\n```\n\nI've looked and haven't found any reports of this error elsewhere.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ngit clone -b stable --depth 1 --single-branch https://github.com/neovim/neovim\ncd neovim\nmake CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSuccessful build\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0 commit a99c469e547fc59472d6d105c0fae323958297a1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A, have not tried to build Vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 16.04.7\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nThe one that ships with Ubuntu, uncustomized\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nsource",
